\end{aligned}
$$

Now, we can substitute this expression for y^3 into the first equation:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& x^3y^2 = 10^{11} \\
& x^3\left(\frac{1000}{x^2}\right) = 10^{11} \\
& x^3 \cdot \frac{1000}{x^2} = 10^{11} \\
& \frac{x^3}{x^2} \cdot 1000 = 10^{11} \\
& \frac{x}{x^2} \cdot 1000 = 10^{11} \\
& \frac{1000}{x} = 10^{11} \\
& x = \frac{1000}{10^{11}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Simplifying, we find that x = 10^{-9}. Therefore, the solution to the system of equations is x = 10^{-9} and y = \frac{1000}{x^2} = 10^{18}.

The answer is: 10^{-9}

